<p><strong>Dr.Gutierrez &lt;<span class="wiki-email">rc.PiCS|zerreitug.b#rc.PiCS|zerreitug.b</span>&gt;</strong><br />
<strong>Tue 2/12/2019&#160;3:35 AM</strong><br />
<strong><span class="wiki-email">ten.PiCS|zevahc.g#ten.PiCS|zevahc.g</span></strong></p>
<p>Gabriel,</p>
<p>You have a problem. While looking for this, it became quickly apparent to me that I'm wading into waters well above my pay grade. This is all I could really get you. Everything else about the project has been scorched from what I can tell. Even this got me nearly detained. I'm fine, but that's about it for favors. Look, I get the interest, considering your department. Even I'm shocked this was going on in our backyard. But whatever happened, they're not bringing this program back, new stones or no new stones.</p>
<p>I'd leave it alone, and don't be surprised if you get called in soon.</p>
<p>Bryan</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">4704_TR13.doc</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&lt;X&gt;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Thaumielic Revision SCP-4704: Proposal #013</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Project Name:</strong> Delta Enclosure</p>
<p><strong>Proposed Utilization:</strong> Implementing SCP-4704 into specialized containment units, outfitted with automated audio cues and positioning mechanisms based on data complied in <em>Position to Tome Relation Guide</em> volumes classified as Adaptive Containment Enclosures (ACEs).</p>
<p>Each individual ACE would be capable of anomalously manipulating the interior of the enclosure. This allows each unit to adapt itself to the necessary requirements dictated by the special containment procedures of the subject it carries, without the need of external resource. This methodology would be self sufficient and has a potential of utilization against vast quantity of entities and objects.</p>
<p>Additionally, ACEs would be capable of disintegrating their contents if so desired. This offers for a humane termination of dangerous or unstable subjects, as well as a fail safe against potential containment breaches.<br /></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>ETHICS COMMITTEE VERDICT:</strong> <span style="color: green">APPROVED</span><br />
<strong>LOGISTICS DEPARTMENT VERDICT:</strong> <span style="color: green">APPROVED</span><br />
<strong>O5 COUNCIL VERDICT:</strong> <span style="color: green">APPROVED</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><iframe src="/inbox/html/b2e5b84994dc0bbe3e659d9f8b63933e29eddd02-1384967927803797880" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" class="html-block-iframe"></iframe></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p>Gabe, if you're reading this, Isaac managed to get the drive to you. I trust him, I hope you do too. They obviously screen everything that gets sent. I considered just giving it to you in person, too risky. Burn the note after you read it, I'd rather not be terminated due to idiotic curiosity and stubbornness. I hate you for turning me on to this, but I owe it to you enough to share what I found.</p>
<p>I'm not sure what to believe anymore.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Gabriel.doc</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&lt;X&gt;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Containment Committee Proposal CASE 91500200</strong><br />
<strong>Adjacent Document #003:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Transcript Of Recorded Conversation Between Doctor Luis Rodolfo Gutierrez and SCP-4704-ö̀ on 2/10/2016</strong></p>
<p>Forward: Text translated from Spanish</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Superfluous Data Redacted</strong></p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> And as long the water maintains this volume it should remain inert. That would be easy enough, yes?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Mmm</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Are you listening? This is important for us.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Are you religious Fito?</p>
<p><em>Dr. Rodolfo sighs</em></p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> I've asked you not to call me that.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Catholic?</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Why?</p>
<p><em>Subject laughs.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> I thought not.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> You seem distracted. Is something wrong?</p>
<p><em>SCP-4704-ö̀ reveals several sheets of Foundation documentation.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> I've been reading these, and I'm confused by something.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> What- Oh for the love of- How did you get those?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> They say that I claim to be Sibú. Just claim, that means you aren't convinced that I am him, right?<br />
<br />
<strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Well&#8230; we can't be sure can we?<br />
<br />
<strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Not sure? You're not sure I'm a god after the things I do?</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> There are more things out there that can do what you do, and they aren't all gods.</p>
<p><em>Subject smiles.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Yes. Interesting. So then, if not a god, what do you think I am?<br />
<br />
<strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Alright. I guess you've earned this much. We would classify you as a reality bender. And we think you're in some way responsible for the stones, as you claim to be. And, at the very least, we know you think you're Sibú.</p>
<p><em>Subject laughs.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Really? You know that for a fact?</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Well don't you?</p>
<p><em>Pause</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> What I think doesn't matter. It never did. All that matters is what you think.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> You've certainly always put a lot of importance on the opinion of others.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> You misunderstand.</p>
<p><em>SCP-4704-ö̀ flips through documentation, arriving to a specific page.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Why do you think the poor Mr. Jones managed to make flowers?</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> You mean the musician? We assumed he got lucky.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Honestly, you people more than anyone ought to know better.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Then how?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> He believed he could.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> What?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> He said as much himself.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong>&#8230;Jones believed the stones were made by some kind of aliens. UFOs. Conspiracies. He was a nut. He knew nothing about-</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> He believed he could make &quot;something beautiful&quot; by playing near the stones, it's all that was needed really.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> It can't be that simple. The position of the stones, the tone he played, if he hadn't accidentally done the worship correctly nothing would've happened. If all he needed was belief then why not us?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Because you never believed it could be that simple.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Do you mean to say it's all been arbitrary?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> You overthought it. The way my kind operate is straight forward. We are born of belief, and we die when we're forgotten. We do whatever your kind thinks we can do. Many years ago your kind thought there was a god named Sibú that molded the Earth for them, and so I am, and so I did.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> If you created man how could man create you?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Have you ever heard of the chicken and the egg?</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Enough! The belief of one mundane person is not enough to bend reality.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Ah, but the belief of many can move mountains. It can make sulfur rain and oceans flood. And sometimes all it takes is a few, maybe even one. One that genuinely believes. [ <em>SCP-4704-ö̀ motions to paper</em> ] a deranged man, or [ <em>SCP-4704-ö̀ motion to Dr. Rodolfo</em> ] a man reading a name.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Me?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> I meant it when I said I had you to thank for being back.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> We've been using the stones far before I ever read about you.</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Yes, thanks to poor Mr. Jones. He had you believe the stones worked with music, and so they did. Then you believed maybe they could be capable of more, and so they were. And then maybe even more. I say, you Foundation folk are prepared to believe anything. I don't blame you, considering the job.</p>
<p><em>SCP-4704-ö̀ reveals another document and begins reading</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Such terrible things you see.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> That's- How are you getting these? We had an agreement!</p>
<p><em>Dr. Rodolfo attempts to take document away from subject, is unsuccessful.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> To answer your prior question, no I don't think I'm Sibú. At least not the Sibú I was. I'm something else now, thanks to you. Something new. A reality bender I think is what you said. The world changed while I was gone, and because of that so have I.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> &#8230;Why reveal this to me? We know now your existence depends on us. Your power. So why tell us so?</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> That's how I used to see it too, but, recently, I realized it isn't so simple.</p>
<p><em>Containment Chamber begins to shake</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> I'm a reality bender now Fito. I'm capable of anything, as long as you believe it. And now you can't help but to believe it.</p>
<p><em>SCP-4704-ö̀ levitates itself and Dr. Rodolfo.</em></p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Wha- How are you-</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> I mean, you can't just stop believing I can do these things. You know that I can. At best you could forget.</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> Stop this! Stop this Sibú!</p>
<p><em>Entirety of Area-92 and surroundings begin to experience a multitude of anomalous transformations. Large portions of site structure are replaced with a limestone replica. Tropical forest overtakes surroundings. There is degeneration of clothing and technology developed after the pre-Columbian Mesoamerica period.</em></p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> As a god I had competition, and I could do what? Change my shape? Control the weather? Mold the Earth? Now I can mold the universe! Thank you, truly, thank you!</p>
<p><strong>Dr. Rodolfo:</strong> If you don't stop we'll forget! We can! We can force everyone, even ourselves!</p>
<p><strong>SCP-4704-ö̀:</strong> Honestly, my friend, why should you? My gifts will help you do many things! They'll help you do anything! You already saw!</p>
<p><em>SCP-4704-ö̀ vanishes. Subsequently, all anomalous transformations underway cease.</em></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Notation:</strong> <em>We gave it this power, so it's our responsibility to diminish it. We tried to maintain a lie with the Neutralized article, but the stones are very much still active, and they require only a thought to cause discrepancies now. We cannot allow ourselves to be bribed by these &quot;gifts&quot;. Destroy them, amnesticize everyone, even the O5. Stop the belief at its roots. - Dr. Rodolfo</em></p>
</blockquote>
